Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.48,0:55:37.52,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}救起19名乘客，开往81号码头{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}Nineteen headed to Pier 81.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.68,0:55:41.12,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们救起了24名乘客，开往皇家港口{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}We got 24 passengers onboard headed to Port Imperial.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.28,0:55:43.24,中文,,0,0,0,,从空中坠入冰冷的哈德逊河\N{\r英文}Whoever has miraculously survived
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.44,0:55:45.56,中文,,0,0,0,,还能奇迹般生还的幸运儿\N{\r英文}this plummet from the skies into the icy Hudson
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.72,0:55:48.76,中文,,0,0,0,,又有300名纽约最优秀的市民前来援助\N{\r英文}has about 300 of New York's finest ready to help them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.92,0:55:52.20,中文,,0,0,0,,唯一的问题是能否救起每一个人\N{\r英文}The only question remaining is will it be too late?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.36,0:55:54.64,中文,,0,0,0,,纽约一台，博比·库萨在曼哈顿的现场报道\N{\r英文}In Manhattan, Bobby Cuza, New York One.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.80,0:55:55.92,中文,,0,0,0,,来，先生，把手给我\N{\r英文}Come on, sir. Give me your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.12,0:55:57.12,中文,,0,0,0,,抓住\N{\r英文}Grab on.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.28,0:55:58.88,中文,,0,0,0,,把手伸给给我，先生，就这样\N{\r英文}Give me your hand, sir. It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.12,0:56:00.53,中文,,0,0,0,,我们抓住你了\N{\r英文}We got you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.24,0:56:03.92,中文,,0,0,0,,- 我的手  - 得赶紧找东西取暖\N{\r英文}- My hands.  - Gotta warm them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.36,0:56:05.96,中文,,0,0,0,,快拿条毛毯给他，快\N{\r英文}Get him a blanket, fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.72,0:56:15.37,中文,,0,0,0,,我还以为自己死定了\N{\r英文}I was sure I was gonna die.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.96,0:56:18.16,中文,,0,0,0,,嘿，今天谁都不会死\N{\r英文}Hey, no one dies today.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.44,0:56:23.72,中文,,0,0,0,,把手给我\N{\r英文}Give me your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.24,0:56:32.64,中文,,0,0,0,,该你了，机长，这里\N{\r英文}Here you go, Captain. This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.96,0:56:35.16,中文,,0,0,0,,抓住我们的手，先生\N{\r英文}Give us your hand, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.32,0:56:36.65,中文,,0,0,0,,萨利，用手臂来抓\N{\r英文}Sully, wrap it around your arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.16,0:56:39.65,中文,,0,0,0,,- 爬上来吧  - 把手给我\N{\r英文}- Climb out now.  - Give me your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.32,0:56:47.12,中文,,0,0,0,,能再拿几条毛毯给我们吗\N{\r英文}Can we get a couple more blankets over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.28,0:56:48.28,中文,,0,0,0,,谢谢你\N{\r英文}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.48,0:56:50.76,中文,,0,0,0,,- 感激不尽  - 没什么\N{\r英文}- Thank you so much.  - You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.24,0:56:52.28,中文,,0,0,0,,请让一让\N{\r英文}Give him some room.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.44,0:56:53.72,中文,,0,0,0,,不客气\N{\r英文}You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.32,0:57:16.36,中文,,0,0,0,,喂\N{\r英文}Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.52,0:57:18.32,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我想跟你报声平安{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}I wanted to call to say I'm okay.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.48,0:57:20.36,中文,,0,0,0,,哦，好，你还是5点50返航?\N{\r英文}Oh, good. Are you still on the 5:50 home?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.52,0:57:21.64,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}发生了一起事故{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}There's been an incident.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.44,0:57:24.84,中文,,0,0,0,,我没事，居然毫发无损\N{\r英文}I'm okay, not a scratch somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.32,0:57:26.60,中文,,0,0,0,,打开电视吧\N{\r英文}Turn on the television.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.88,0:57:29.04,中文,,0,0,0,,你让我打开电视是什么意思？\N{\r英文}What do you mean "Turn on the television"?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.36,0:57:30.69,中文,,0,0,0,,洛丽，我现在不方便说话\N{\r英文}Lorrie, I can't talk right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.88,0:57:33.04,中文,,0,0,0,,等码头这里平静下来我再打给你\N{\r英文}I will call you from the pier when things quiet down.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.52,0:57:37.17,中文,,0,0,0,,我被迫在哈德逊河上降落\N{\r英文}I had to land in the Hudson.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.36,0:57:40.56,中文,,0,0,0,,萨利，我没听明白\N{\r英文}Sully, I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.96,0:57:44.56,中文,,0,0,0,,我爱你，我也平安，跟女儿报下我平安\N{\r英文}I love you, and I'm okay. Tell the girls I am okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.40,0:57:48.00,中文,,0,0,0,,我得挂了\N{\r英文}But I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.12,0:57:51.72,中文,,0,0,0,,姑娘，快打开电视\N{\r英文}Girls, turn on the TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.40,0:57:56.52,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一架全美航空的客机坠入哈德逊河{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}An extensive rescue effort is underway{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.68,0:57:59.88,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}迫使机上乘客竞相逃命{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}after a US Airways Flight crashes into the Hudson River,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.08,0:58:02.60,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- 目前一场大搜救行动正在进行当中  - 天啊{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}-sending passengers scrambling for safety. -Oh, my God.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.24,0:58:25.57,中文,,0,0,0,,把你们的湿衣服脱了\N{\r英文}If you have any wet clothing on, take it off
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.72,0:58:27.92,中文,,0,0,0,,去红十字那拿条毛毯御寒\N{\r英文}and wrap up in a blanket from the Red Cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.44,0:58:40.44,中文,,0,0,0,,你会没事的，露西尔\N{\r英文}You're gonna be okay. Okay, Lucille?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.60,0:58:43.08,中文,,0,0,0,,这就把你送上救护车，好吗？\N{\r英文}I'm gonna take you right to the ambulance, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.00,0:58:48.28,中文,,0,0,0,,或许他已经上来了，或许比我们还先到\N{\r英文}Maybe he's here. Maybe he beat us somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.84,0:58:51.68,中文,,0,0,0,,有很多船参与救援，杰夫！\N{\r英文}There's lots of boats! Jeff!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.24,0:58:55.24,中文,,0,0,0,,萨利！\N{\r英文}Sully!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.48,0:58:56.52,中文,,0,0,0,,丹！\N{\r英文}Dan!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.20,0:59:03.88,中文,,0,0,0,,丹，我得知道有谁受了伤以及伤情程度，还需要总人数\N{\r英文}Dan, I need to know who's hurt and how badly, and I need a count.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.04,0:59:06.69,中文,,0,0,0,,155，那是我要的数字，全体乘客和机组人员的总和\N{\r英文}155, that's my number. That's passengers and crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.84,0:59:08.33,中文,,0,0,0,,好，你怎么样？\N{\r英文}Okay. How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.52,0:59:11.04,中文,,0,0,0,,等我们统计到155就会回答你\N{\r英文}I'll answer that question when we've counted 155.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.20,0:59:12.28,中文,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\r英文}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.48,0:59:14.24,中文,,0,0,0,,亲爱的，是我\N{\r英文}Honey, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.36,0:59:17.52,中文,,0,0,0,,差不多吧，我今晚就回家\N{\r英文}Sort of. I won't be home tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.36,0:59:22.01,中文,,0,0,0,,谢莉，现在跟你通话就好像做梦一样\N{\r英文}Sherri, I cannot believe lam talking to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.52,0:59:31.20,中文,,0,0,0,,机长，上级要我现在把你送去见布隆伯格市长\N{\r英文}Captain. I'm here to escort you to meet with Mayor Bloomberg
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.36,0:59:32.93,中文,,0,0,0,,和警察局长雷蒙德·凯利\N{\r英文}and Police Commissioner Raymond Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.08,0:59:34.96,中文,,0,0,0,,要是市长想打声招呼，他得亲自跑一趟了\N{\r英文}If the Mayor wants to say hello, he'll have to come down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.12,0:59:36.12,中文,,0,0,0,,我们这还忙着工作呢\N{\r英文}We're still working.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.28,0:59:38.40,中文,,0,0,0,,萨利，我会帮你统计的\N{\r英文}Sully, I can keep assembling the count.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.04,0:59:40.04,中文,,0,0,0,,杰夫\N{\r英文}Jeff.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.20,0:59:42.20,中文,,0,0,0,,杰夫，我需要总人数，我们得立即去办\N{\r英文}Jeff, I need a count. We've gotta have a count.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.36,0:59:43.69,中文,,0,0,0,,萨利，现在是不可能统计出总人数的\N{\r英文}There's no way to get a real count out here, Sully.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.24,0:59:45.24,中文,,0,0,0,,萨利，杰夫说得对\N{\r英文}Sully, Jeff's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.40,0:59:47.24,中文,,0,0,0,,还是先给你找几件干衣服穿上吧，不然你要冻坏了\N{\r英文}Let's get you in some dry clothes before you freeze to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.40,0:59:50.00,中文,,0,0,0,,机长，市长和局长凯利亲自来这里见你如何？\N{\r英文}Captain, what if the Mayor and Chief Kelly come down here to meet with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.28,0:59:52.16,中文,,0,0,0,,丹，因为这是架国内航班\N{\r英文}Dan, because it was a domestic flight。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.32,0:59:53.68,中文,,0,0,0,,对，所以我们没有旅客名单\N{\r英文}Yeah, we got no manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.84,0:59:56.57,中文,,0,0,0,,我们得一个个的查旅客信息，才有可能做出统计\N{\r英文}We're gonna have to track the passenger information down one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.72,0:59:58.00,中文,,0,0,0,,- 你能帮忙吗？  - 可以\N{\r英文}- Can you help?  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.16,0:59:59.84,中文,,0,0,0,,我马上给约翰·凯里打电话，会帮你统计出总人数\N{\r英文}I'm gonna call John Carey. We're gonna get you a count.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.28,1:00:02.85,中文,,0,0,0,,萨利听我一句，你已经尽心尽力了，现在就让我来接手吧\N{\r英文}But, Sully, listen. You've done enough. Let me take it from here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.48,1:00:16.56,中文,,0,0,0,,- 杰夫？  - {\i1}老爸!{\i}\N{\r英文}- Jeff?  - {\i1}Pop!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.72,1:00:17.84,中文,,0,0,0,,我没事\N{\r英文}I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.00,1:00:20.00,中文,,0,0,0,,我在另一边的机翼上，救援人员接我到了新泽西\N{\r英文}I was on the other wing. They brought us to Jersey.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.40,1:00:23.40,中文,,0,0,0,,我看不到你，也找不到你\N{\r英文}I couldn't see you. I couldn't find you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.56,1:00:25.36,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我听见你一直在喊我的名字{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}I could hear you shouting my name the whole time.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.64,1:00:28.36,中文,,0,0,0,,我也喊回去的，我猜河水...\N{\r英文}I shouted back. I guess the river...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.88,1:00:29.88,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你没事吧？{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}Are you okay?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.04,1:00:31.32,中文,,0,0,0,,我爱你，儿子\N{\r英文}I love you, son.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.12,1:00:34.92,中文,,0,0,0,,我也爱你\N{\r英文}I love you, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.88,1:00:37.56,中文,,0,0,0,,我们竟然大难不死\N{\r英文}Can you believe we made it?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.00,1:00:41.72,中文,,0,0,0,,飞机坠落\N{\r英文}I mean, the plane crashed
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.88,1:00:43.68,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}到河里{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}on the river!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.96,1:00:45.45,中文,,0,0,0,,这谁敢相信？\N{\r英文}Are you kidding me?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.64,1:00:50.64,中文,,0,0,0,,真是难以置信\N{\r英文}Ah, so unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.32,1:01:11.52,中文,,0,0,0,,我从未如此开心自己能回到纽约\N{\r英文}I've never been so happy to be in New York in my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.00,1:01:24.00,中文,,0,0,0,,嘿，帕蒂\N{\r英文}Hey, Patty.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.32,1:01:25.60,中文,,0,0,0,,主管让我来找你\N{\r英文}Supe sent me looking for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.76,1:01:27.25,中文,,0,0,0,,在上面大家都很激动\N{\r英文}Everyone's going nuts up top.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.40,1:01:29.60,中文,,0,0,0,,- 你不去吗？  - 我猜你还不知道吧\N{\r英文}- Aren't you coming?  - I guess you didn't hear.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.76,1:01:32.24,中文,,0,0,0,,我的全美航空1549掉到哈德逊河里了\N{\r英文}I lost Cactus 1549 in the Hudson.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.00,1:01:36.16,中文,,0,0,0,,哈，我猜你还没听说吧，他水面迫降成功\N{\r英文}Huh. I guess you haven't heard. He landed the son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.44,1:01:37.68,中文,,0,0,0,,什么？\N{\r英文}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.88,1:01:40.28,中文,,0,0,0,,所有人都得救了，奇迹再现啊\N{\r英文}Everyone's been pulled off. It's a miracle!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.44,1:01:42.32,中文,,0,0,0,,我还以为他们机毁人亡了\N{\r英文}I thought I lost them all.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.48,1:01:44.60,中文,,0,0,0,,- 这里肯定有电视的吧  - 肯定有\N{\r英文}- They've got to get a TV in here.  - Yeah. Seriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.08,1:01:49.24,中文,,0,0,0,,我脉搏多少？\N{\r英文}What is my pulse rate?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.84,1:01:51.44,中文,,0,0,0,,110\N{\r英文}It's 110.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.16,1:01:54.04,中文,,0,0,0,,我正常脉搏是55\N{\r英文}My normal resting is 55.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.20,1:01:55.44,中文,,0,0,0,,110\N{\r英文}110...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.24,1:01:57.57,中文,,0,0,0,,不太妙啊\N{\r英文}That's not good.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.72,1:02:00.24,中文,,0,0,0,,你说得对，110是不妙\N{\r英文}You are right. 110 is not good.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.44,1:02:03.72,中文,,0,0,0,,可你刚从鬼门关走了一遭，110已经是相当不错了\N{\r英文}After what you just went through, 110 is extraordinary.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.88,1:02:05.68,中文,,0,0,0,,多琳的情况如何？\N{\r英文}How is Doreen?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.84,1:02:07.28,中文,,0,0,0,,割了道深口子\N{\r英文}Fairly severe laceration.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.44,1:02:09.04,中文,,0,0,0,,我们会留院观察她一两天，以防感染\N{\r英文}But we'll keep her a day or two to stem the infection.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.24,1:02:10.36,中文,,0,0,0,,那她不会有其他问题了？\N{\r英文}But she'll be okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.52,1:02:12.88,中文,,0,0,0,,她会留下个伤疤，还有个英雄事迹可传颂\N{\r英文}She'll have a scar and a hell of a story to tell.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.08,1:02:14.08,中文,,0,0,0,,可能没人会相信她\N{\r英文}Although no one'll believe her.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.24,1:02:16.52,中文,,0,0,0,,呵呵，你现在就站在我面前，可我仍然不敢相信\N{\r英文}Hell, I'm standing here with you right now and I don't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.68,1:02:18.36,中文,,0,0,0,,你把飞机降落在哈德逊河上，尽然能毫发无损\N{\r英文}You landed a plane on the Hudson. Not a scratch on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.52,1:02:19.56,中文,,0,0,0,,阿尼\N{\r英文}Arnie.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.96,1:02:23.77,中文,,0,0,0,,工会今天把重量级人物都派出来了啊？\N{\r英文}The union is pulling out all the big guns today, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.24,1:02:26.57,中文,,0,0,0,,我刚跟丹·布里特谈过，萨利\N{\r英文}Talked to Dan Britt, Sully.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.68,1:02:28.96,中文,,0,0,0,,有总人数了？\N{\r英文}Got a count.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.96,1:02:31.24,中文,,0,0,0,,155.\N{\r英文}155.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.92,1:02:35.16,中文,,0,0,0,,155.\N{\r英文}155.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.32,1:02:36.52,中文,,0,0,0,,是正式的数字\N{\r英文}It's official.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.76,1:02:38.76,中文,,0,0,0,,- 155  - 155\N{\r英文}-155.  -155.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.92,1:02:44.33,中文,,0,0,0,,155\N{\r英文}155.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.92,1:02:46.57,中文,,0,0,0,,谢谢你，阿尼\N{\r英文}Thank you, Arnie.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.44,1:03:20.28,中文,,0,0,0,,- 嘿，卡尔  - 杰夫\N{\r英文}- Hey, Carl.  - Jeff.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.44,1:03:22.80,中文,,0,0,0,,- 萨利  - 卡尔\N{\r英文}- Sully.  - Carl.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.96,1:03:24.72,中文,,0,0,0,,你今天的表演可真是惊世骇俗啊\N{\r英文}Hell of a thing you pulled off out there today.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.88,1:03:25.92,中文,,0,0,0,,呃，我们在这里了\N{\r英文}Well, we're here.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.08,1:03:27.96,中文,,0,0,0,,我也就不想那么多了\N{\r英文}It's about all I know at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.44,1:03:30.04,中文,,0,0,0,,哦，这位是梅女士，酒店的人\N{\r英文}Oh, this is Ms. May, with the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.24,1:03:31.65,中文,,0,0,0,,想跟你们聊两句\N{\r英文}Wanted to have a quick word with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.80,1:03:33.04,中文,,0,0,0,,我不会占用两位先生太多时间\N{\r英文}I won't take your time, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.24,1:03:34.32,中文,,0,0,0,,我来这就是想跟你们说明，我和酒店员工\N{\r英文}This is only to say that my staff and I
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.48,1:03:35.72,中文,,0,0,0,,绝对会保护你们的隐私\N{\r英文}are committed to protecting your privacy.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.88,1:03:38.40,中文,,0,0,0,,所以，需要我做什么尽管开口\N{\r英文}So, if there's anything I can do at all...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.56,1:03:41.72,中文,,0,0,0,,如果可以，今晚你们把我的制服拿去干洗一下吧\N{\r英文}If it's possible, I'd love to have my uniform dry-cleaned overnight.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.92,1:03:43.33,中文,,0,0,0,,我就只有这身衣服\N{\r英文}It's the only clothing that I have.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.48,1:03:44.48,中文,,0,0,0,,干洗？\N{\r英文}Dry-cleaning?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.64,1:03:46.24,中文,,0,0,0,,如果要求过分了点，又或者时间太晚\N{\r英文}If it's too much... If it's too late...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.40,1:03:47.56,中文,,0,0,0,,你不是开玩笑吧？\N{\r英文}Are you kidding?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.76,1:03:50.60,中文,,0,0,0,,萨伦伯格机长，如果可以我连整座酒店都可以包给你\N{\r英文}Captain Sullenberger, I'd give you this whole hotel if I could.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.32,1:03:54.40,中文,,0,0,0,,好了\N{\r英文}Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.44,1:03:57.60,中文,,0,0,0,,谢谢你，伊夫林，非常感谢\N{\r英文}Well, thank you, Evelyn. Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.76,1:03:59.60,中文,,0,0,0,,- 为了萨利做什么都行  - 好\N{\r英文}- Anything for Sully.  - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.76,1:04:01.17,中文,,0,0,0,,希望你们住得愉快\N{\r英文}Have a blessed day.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.60,1:04:04.96,中文,,0,0,0,,刚才是怎么一回事？\N{\r英文}What just happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.12,1:04:07.36,中文,,0,0,0,,陌生人第一次见面就主动抱你啊\N{\r英文}You just got hugged by a total stranger.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.76,1:04:10.28,中文,,0,0,0,,走吧，萨利\N{\r英文}Ah, come on, Sully.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.44,1:04:12.44,中文,,0,0,0,,你上一次听说有人把喷气式飞机降落在水上\N{\r英文}When's the last time you heard of someone
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.60,1:04:14.60,中文,,0,0,0,,然后所有人都生还的\N{\r英文}landing a jet plane on the water
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.12,1:04:16.45,中文,,0,0,0,,还是哪个朝代的事？\N{\r英文}and everybody lived?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.92,1:04:19.96,中文,,0,0,0,,我说的没错吧\N{\r英文}Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.44,1:04:24.12,中文,,0,0,0,,我给你们拿了剃须膏，剃须刀片，牙刷\N{\r英文}I got shaving cream, razor blades, toothpaste.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.48,1:04:27.28,中文,,0,0,0,,还有新衣服\N{\r英文}And new clothes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.80,1:04:30.84,中文,,0,0,0,,你觉得我们俩是忍者？\N{\r英文}What, did you think we were ninjas?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.00,1:04:32.68,中文,,0,0,0,,只有凯马特还开着门\N{\r英文}Kmart was the only store open.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.84,1:04:34.00,中文,,0,0,0,,这里是皇后区，又是夜里10点\N{\r英文}It's Queens. It's 10:00 in the evening.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.16,1:04:36.64,中文,,0,0,0,,- 布鲁克斯兄弟（美国服装品牌）早关门了  - 嗯\N{\r英文}- You find a Brooks Brothers.  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.12,1:04:39.12,中文,,0,0,0,,萨利\N{\r英文}Sully.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.80,1:04:41.56,中文,,0,0,0,,你干嘛还穿着制服？\N{\r英文}What are you even still doing in uniform?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.80,1:04:43.56,中文,,0,0,0,,我也不知道\N{\r英文}Ah. You know, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.72,1:04:47.32,中文,,0,0,0,,你们俩今天都忙了一整天，早点休息好吗？\N{\r英文}Look, guys. It's been a long day. Why don't you get some rest?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.48,1:04:51.32,中文,,0,0,0,,麦克·克利里明早8点过来，你们俩到时要做好准备\N{\r英文}Mike Cleary will be over in the 8 a.m. and make sure you're both doing okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.12,1:04:54.28,中文,,0,0,0,,- 谢谢你，卡尔  - 也谢谢你，机长\N{\r英文}- Thank you, Carl.  - Yeah, thank you, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.04,1:04:57.48,中文,,0,0,0,,纽约好长时间都没这种好消息了\N{\r英文}It's been a while since New York had news this good.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.28,1:05:00.52,中文,,0,0,0,,特别是和飞机有关的\N{\r英文}Especially with an airplane in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.36,1:05:11.85,中文,,0,0,0,,明天见，萨利\N{\r英文}I'll see you later, Sully.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.25,1:05:28.95,中文,,0,0,0,,宁可延误，不酿灾难
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.28,1:05:37.60,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}市政官员不断提及的一个词是“时机”{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}The word city officials keep repeating is "timing."{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.76,1:05:40.88,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}纽约警察局潜水小队和拖船船长{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}The perfect timing of the NYPD scuba units{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.08,1:05:43.08,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}到达现场的绝佳时机{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}and of the ferry boat captains,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.24,1:05:47.40,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当然还有机长不可思议的精确时机{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}and of course, the inexplicably precise timing of the pilot.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.56,1:05:50.96,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}萨伦伯格，萨利机长，就在不经意间{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}Captain "Sully" Sullenberger, who, with almost no time,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.12,1:05:53.36,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}成为了永恒的符号{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}became a man for all time.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.60,1:05:54.60,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是克莉斯汀·约翰逊...{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}This is Kristine Johnson...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.84,1:05:55.84,中文,,0,0,0,,时机\N{\r英文}The timing.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.04,1:05:57.56,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在哈德逊河进行的现场报道{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}...reporting live from the Hudson River.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.80,1:05:58.80,中文,,0,0,0,,纽约一台\N{\r英文}New York One Minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.00,1:06:00.92,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}海岸警卫队放出一段1549号航班{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}The coast guard released this new video of Flight 1549{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.16,1:06:03.12,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}紧急降落在哈德逊河的新影像{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}making its emergency landing on the Hudson.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.28,1:06:06.20,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}与此同时，飞机发动机的搜寻工作也正在展开{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}Meanwhile, the search is launched for the engine of the aircraft.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.96,1:06:10.56,中文,,0,0,0,,嘿，萨利，让我...\N{\r英文}Hey, Sully. Let me...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.72,1:06:19.13,中文,,0,0,0,,快接啊\N{\r英文}Come on. Answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.80,1:06:20.92,中文,,0,0,0,,接啊！\N{\r英文}Answer!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.76,1:06:25.44,中文,,0,0,0,,拉里，驾驶舱通话记录器的听证会还有不到2天就要开了，你能多快帮我个忙？\N{\r英文}Larry, the CVR is in two days. How fast can you arrange a favor?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.68,1:06:26.72,中文,,0,0,0,,萨利？\N{\r英文}Sully?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.96,1:06:30.56,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我知道空客已经把S22模拟的时间安排发给了工厂{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}I know that Airbus has simulations scheduled for the S22 sim at the factory.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.72,1:06:34.32,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}可那是下周在图卢兹，你能让他们重新安排时间吗?{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}But that's next week in Toulouse. Can you get them to reschedule?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.48,1:06:35.76,中文,,0,0,0,,现在是凌晨1点半\N{\r英文}It's 1:30 in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.92,1:06:37.04,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我需要你把它改到{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}I need you to make it happen{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.24,1:06:38.65,中文,,0,0,0,,我们听驾驶舱通话录音之前\N{\r英文}before we listen to the CVR.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.80,1:06:40.76,中文,,0,0,0,,在我们的证词完成之前\N{\r英文}Before our testimony is complete.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.92,1:06:42.08,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}为什么？{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}Why?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.76,1:06:45.65,中文,,0,0,0,,观看计算机模拟是我的权利，而且我感觉\N{\r英文}I have a right to see the simulations and I have a feeling that
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.80,1:06:49.16,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}人类驾驶员和计算机有着本质区别，结果可能会大不相同{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}with human pilots and not a computer, the results are going to be different.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.32,1:06:51.76,中文,,0,0,0,,如果它们给出的结果是一模一样呢？\N{\r英文}What if they show the exact same result?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.08,1:06:55.28,中文,,0,0,0,,如果一样，我就退休不干了\N{\r英文}If they do, then I'll hand you my wings myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.44,1:06:56.80,中文,,0,0,0,,这一切都关系到时机，拉里\N{\r英文}It's all about the timing, Larry.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.96,1:06:58.92,中文,,0,0,0,,不需要赶时间的话，你什么事情都能办好\N{\r英文}You can accomplish anything if you're never in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.08,1:07:00.84,中文,,0,0,0,,我要举双手赞成\N{\r英文}I sure as hell agree with that.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.00,1:07:03.32,中文,,0,0,0,,驾驶舱通话记录仪的听证会是在周三，那只有36个小时了\N{\r英文}The CVR is on Wednesday. That's 36 hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.48,1:07:04.81,中文,,0,0,0,,你能办妥吗？\N{\r英文}Can you make it happen?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.96,1:07:07.61,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我尽力，可能要打爆电话了{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}I'll try. It's a lot of phone calls to make.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.76,1:07:09.28,中文,,0,0,0,,现在法国已经是早上7点半了\N{\r英文}It's already 7:30 in the morning in France,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.44,1:07:10.56,中文,,0,0,0,,你最好马上开始吧\N{\r英文}so you better get started.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.72,1:07:12.60,中文,,0,0,0,,谢谢你，拉里，谢谢\N{\r英文}Thank you, Larry. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.80,1:07:22.90,中文,,0,0,0,,美国运输部\N{\r英文}美国联邦航空管理局
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.40,1:07:32.40,中文,,0,0,0,,嘿，洛丽\N{\r英文}Hey, Lorrie
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.60,1:07:35.68,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}嗨，抱歉听证会前还要来打搅你{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}Hi. I'm sorry to bother you before the hearing.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.84,1:07:38.28,中文,,0,0,0,,亲爱的，出什么事了？\N{\r英文}Sweetheart, what happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.56,1:07:45.28,中文,,0,0,0,,就刚刚，我才第一次意识到，有...\N{\r英文}I realized just now, for the first time, that there were...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.20,1:07:50.20,中文,,0,0,0,,那机上有155人，而你就是其中之一\N{\r英文}There were 155 people on that plane and you were one of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.56,1:07:53.44,中文,,0,0,0,,我们差点失去你\N{\r英文}We almost lost you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.08,1:07:57.08,中文,,0,0,0,,可你们没有啊，我还好好的\N{\r英文}Yeah, but you didn't. I'm right here.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.72,1:08:00.48,中文,,0,0,0,,你能挺得住吗\N{\r英文}How are you holding up?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.68,1:08:02.20,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我能得挺住{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}Oh, I'm holding up.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.36,1:08:04.24,中文,,0,0,0,,这个难关就要过去了吗?\N{\r英文}Please tell me this is almost over.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.76,1:08:06.33,中文,,0,0,0,,这个难关就要过去了\N{\r英文}It's almost over.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.48,1:08:07.52,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}好{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}Okay.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.68,1:08:08.80,中文,,0,0,0,,我爱你\N{\r英文}I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.96,1:08:10.37,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我也爱你{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}I love you, too.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.56,1:08:12.72,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我这边完事了再给你打电话{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}I'll call you when they're done with me.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.72,1:08:18.72,中文,,0,0,0,,国家运输安全委员会
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.36,1:08:43.32,中文,,0,0,0,,- 萨利  - 让我们开始吧，拉里\N{\r英文}- Sully.  - Let's go, Larry.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.00,1:08:56.36,中文,,0,0,0,,- 早上好，萨利  - 杰夫\N{\r英文}- Good morning, Sully.  - Jeff.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.92,1:08:58.36,中文,,0,0,0,,早上好，各位先生和女士，欢迎光临\N{\r英文}Good morning, ladies and gentlemen, and welcome.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.56,1:08:59.72,中文,,0,0,0,,我是查尔斯·波特\N{\r英文}My name is Charles Porter.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.92,1:09:02.57,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}国家运输安全委员会指派我来{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}I've been assigned by the National Transportation Safety Board{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.76,1:09:05.08,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}主持今天的公众听证会{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}to conduct this public hearing here today.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.40,1:09:07.16,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们今天要涵盖的内容很多{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}We have a lot of material to cover.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.72,1:09:10.40,中文,,0,0,0,,但在我们听驾驶舱通话录音之前\N{\r英文}But before we listen to the cockpit voice recording...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.56,1:09:12.44,中文,,0,0,0,,我们将会首次同这2位先生\N{\r英文}And we will be listening to it for the first time
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.60,1:09:14.09,中文,,0,0,0,,一起聆听\N{\r英文}along with you, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.24,1:09:17.60,中文,,0,0,0,,应机长萨伦伯格和工会的请求\N{\r英文}Per the request of Captain Sullenberger and the union,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.76,1:09:20.00,中文,,0,0,0,,空中客车公司同意经由卫星\N{\r英文}Airbus has agreed to link us via satellite
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.16,1:09:22.24,中文,,0,0,0,,向我们传输今天的模拟飞行演示\N{\r英文}to today's piloted simulations.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.40,1:09:24.08,中文,,0,0,0,,请开启传输\N{\r英文}Upload link, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.92,1:09:26.57,中文,,0,0,0,,只是模拟罢了，萨利\N{\r英文}They're just simulations, Sully.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.76,1:09:29.00,中文,,0,0,0,,这不会改变我对那天的看法\N{\r英文}Won't change my mind about what happened up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.68,1:09:31.40,中文,,0,0,0,,可能会改变他们的\N{\r英文}Might change theirs.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.00,1:09:42.04,中文,,0,0,0,,鸟群\N{\r英文}Birds.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.96,1:09:45.61,中文,,0,0,0,,1发减速，2发也减速了\N{\r英文}Number one's rolling back. And number two.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.76,1:09:46.92,中文,,0,0,0,,自动驾驶关闭\N{\r英文}Auto pilot's off.
