Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.32,1:13:04.60,中文,,0,0,0,,好像去取牛奶一样简单\N{\r英文}"like you're going back to pick up the milk."
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.24,1:13:08.13,中文,,0,0,0,,这是在853米的高度遭遇双发停车后\N{\r英文}This was dual engine loss at 2,800 feet
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.32,1:13:10.48,中文,,0,0,0,,立即执行水面迫降\N{\r英文}followed by an immediate water landing
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.64,1:13:13.24,中文,,0,0,0,,机上还载有155条鲜活的生命\N{\r英文}with 155 souls onboard.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.40,1:13:17.20,中文,,0,0,0,,没人接受过此类事故的训练\N{\r英文}No one has ever trained for an incident like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.36,1:13:18.36,中文,,0,0,0,,没人\N{\r英文}No one.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.40,1:13:22.68,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}以那样不切实际的倾斜角在泰特伯勒机场降落{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}The Teterboro landing, with its unrealistic bank angle{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.96,1:13:25.24,中文,,0,0,0,,我们可不是雷鸟飞行表演队（特技飞行）\N{\r英文}we were not the Thunderbirds up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.76,1:13:28.08,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我想知道这个机长对这个动作进行了多少次练习{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}I'd like to know how many times the pilot practiced that maneuver{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.24,1:13:30.32,中文,,0,0,0,,才能不出差错的成功降落\N{\r英文}before he actually pulled it off.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.60,1:13:33.20,中文,,0,0,0,,我不是在质疑这些机长的技术\N{\r英文}I'm not questioning the pilots.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.36,1:13:34.80,中文,,0,0,0,,他们都是技术过硬的\N{\r英文}They're good pilots.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.88,1:13:38.88,中文,,0,0,0,,可他们明显受过指示，在遭遇鸟击后\N{\r英文}But they've clearly been instructed to head for the airport
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.04,1:13:40.84,中文,,0,0,0,,就立即返回机场\N{\r英文}immediately after the bird strike.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.36,1:13:44.17,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这里面没有分析和决策过程{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}You've allowed no time for analysis or decision-making.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.60,1:13:48.52,中文,,0,0,0,,所有的计算机模拟，你们都把人类因素排除在驾驶舱外\N{\r英文}In these simulations, you've taken all of the humanity out of the cockpit.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.48,1:13:53.56,中文,,0,0,0,,这些机长花了多少时间来准备此类事件？\N{\r英文}How much time did the pilots spend planning for this event?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.72,1:13:55.29,中文,,0,0,0,,来准备这些模拟？\N{\r英文}For these simulations?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.76,1:14:01.12,中文,,0,0,0,,你们要是想找人为错误\N{\r英文}You are looking for human error.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.52,1:14:04.24,中文,,0,0,0,,就把人也考虑进去\N{\r英文}Then make it human.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.20,1:14:11.28,中文,,0,0,0,,这可不是电子游戏\N{\r英文}This wasn't a video game.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.44,1:14:13.20,中文,,0,0,0,,是生死攸关的\N{\r英文}It was life and death.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.76,1:14:15.92,中文,,0,0,0,,萨利的真知灼见，值得你们好好掂量\N{\r英文}Sully's right. That's worth a few seconds.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.08,1:14:18.52,中文,,0,0,0,,请问下那些机长练习了多少次？\N{\r英文}Please ask how many practice runs they had.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.44,1:14:20.93,中文,,0,0,0,,17次\N{\r英文}Seventeen.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.08,1:14:28.80,中文,,0,0,0,,17次\N{\r英文}Seventeen?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.04,1:14:35.57,中文,,0,0,0,,降落在泰特伯勒的机长之前有过17次尝试\N{\r英文}The pilot who landed at Teterboro had 17 practice attempts
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.72,1:14:38.40,中文,,0,0,0,,{\i1}才有我们刚观看的模拟结果{\i}\N{\r英文}{\i1}before the simulation we just witnessed.{\i}
